        <main class="px-3">
            <h1 class="mb-4"><strong>About Us</strong></h1>
            <div class="row">
                <h4 class="text-center">What is Liberty Education?</h4>
                <div class="col-12 text-start">
                    <p class="lead text-start">It’s a micro-school that is open to the public and allows
                        for the opportunity to have a tiny class with 6-12 students with individualized
                        curriculum and lots of one-on-one attention. In this uncharted and unfamiliar
                        season where we aren’t sure exactly what school will look like, and if or when
                        it will close and go back to online school at home, this is an opportunity to
                        eliminate many of those risks.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
                <h4 class="text-center">What does the school look like?</h4>
                <div class="col-12 text-start">
                    <p class="lead text-start">It is a 3rd-6th grade class. The beauty of such a small class, with
                        parents
                        who are invested in their child’s experience and education is that we can plan much of the
                        curriculum
                        based on the students’ interests.

                        Of course we cover the basics of grade level math, grammar, writing and reading comprehension
                        and we have the ability to work one-on-one with each student several times during the week to
                        help
                        them fill in gaps and ensure that they are progressing at whatever speed they are capable of. We
                        cover history, geography, and science through project based learning.

                        We spend time outside every day. We build social skills within their age group, and discuss
                        making healthy choices. We have a little less than a half acre and have several animals, a
                        garden,
                        basketball hoop, swing set and room to play and run. We have art lessons from a professional
                        artist and Spanish lessons from a native speaker. Fridays are Adventure Days. With such a small
                        group we can go pretty much anywhere, and you and your children can help determine where we
                        explore!

                    </p>
                </div>
